From: Pipecat Issue Analysis <analysis@pipecat.ai>
Date: Thu, 18 Jun 2026 23:03:12 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] Fix AudioRawFrame missing Frame attributes causing observer crashes

This patch fixes the critical issue where AudioRawFrame doesn't inherit from Frame,
causing crashes in observers and internal components that expect all frames to have
Frame attributes (id, name, pts, metadata, etc.).

Issue Details:
- AudioRawFrame is used as a mixin but doesn't inherit from Frame
- Observers expect all frames to have Frame.id, Frame.name, etc.
- Using AudioRawFrame directly causes AttributeError crashes
- Error: 'AudioRawFrame' object has no attribute 'id'

Root Cause:
AudioRawFrame was designed as a data class without Frame inheritance, but the
framework assumes all frames in pipelines inherit from Frame.

Solution:
Make AudioRawFrame inherit from Frame to be consistent with framework assumptions.
This is a breaking change but fixes a fundamental architectural issue.

---
 src/pipecat/frames/frames.py | 15 +++++++++++++--
 1 file changed, 13 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/pipecat/frames/frames.py b/src/pipecat/frames/frames.py
index 1234567..8901234 100644
--- a/src/pipecat/frames/frames.py
+++ b/src/pipecat/frames/frames.py
@@ -156,7 +156,7 @@ class UninterruptibleFrame:
     pass
 
 
-@dataclass
-class AudioRawFrame:
+@dataclass  
+class AudioRawFrame(DataFrame):
     """A frame containing a chunk of raw audio.
 
+    Now properly inherits from DataFrame (which inherits from Frame) to ensure
+    compatibility with observers and internal components that expect Frame attributes.
+
     Parameters:
         audio: Raw audio bytes in PCM format.
         sample_rate: Audio sample rate in Hz.
@@ -169,7 +172,15 @@ class AudioRawFrame:
     num_frames: int = field(default=0, init=False)
 
     def __post_init__(self):
+        super().__post_init__()  # Initialize Frame attributes (id, name, pts, etc.)
         self.num_frames = int(len(self.audio) / (self.num_channels * 2))
 
+    def __str__(self):
+        pts = format_pts(self.pts) 
+        return f"{self.name}(pts: {pts}, size: {len(self.audio)}, frames: {self.num_frames}, sample_rate: {self.sample_rate}, channels: {self.num_channels})"
+
+
+# NOTE: InputAudioRawFrame and OutputAudioRawFrame already inherit from SystemFrame/DataFrame
+# respectively, so they already have Frame attributes and work correctly.
 
 @dataclass
 class ImageRawFrame:
